The bound~\eqref{eq:thm-general-converse} is in general difficult to compute or analyze. 


Next, we prove a converse bound, which is motivated by the converse  in~\cite{tyagi2015-05a} for secret key generation. This bound is both numerically and analytically  tractable. 
\begin{thm}
\label{thm:converse-wei}
Let $Q_{Y|Z}: \setY\to\setZ$ be an arbitrary random transformation. Then, every $(M,{\epsilon},{\delta})$ secrecy code for the wiretap channel  $(\setX, P_{YZ|X}, \setY\times\setZ)$ satisfies 
\begin{IEEEeqnarray}{rCl}
M\leq \inf_{\tau \in(0, 1-{\epsilon} -{\delta}) } \frac{\tau +{\delta}}{\tau \beta_{1-{\epsilon}-{\delta} -\tau} (P_{XYZ}, P_{XZ}Q_{Y|Z}) } \IEEEeqnarraynumspace
\label{eq:converse-bound-general}
