To prove~\eqref{eq:thm-ach-expansion-awgn}, we shall choose $P_{X^n}$ to be the uniform distribution over the power sphere $\setS_n \define \{x^n\in \realset^n:  \|x^n\|^2 = nP\}$ and set $Q_{Z^n} \sim \mathcal{N}(\mathbf{0}, (P+N_2)\matI_n) $. For such a $P_{X^n}$ it was shown in~\cite{tan15-05-a} that there exists an

